CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 7, 1956, page 18, reads: "5. The Bell Telephone Company installed live telephones in their booth. Hosteses [sic] Doris Thomas and Barbara Thompson are shown here with representatives, Rodger [sic] Drake, Charles Jackson, Norman Back and Bob Bayer."
TitMainTitle: Men, and women, including Doris Thomas wearing eyeglasses and name tag, and Barbara Thompson holding notebook, gathered in Bell Telephone Company booth in Syria Mosque for the 1956 Pittsburgh Courier Home Service Fair
